The paper discusses the use of spiking neural networks (SNN) for audio and image recognition tasks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The use of phase-change memory synapses for implementing parallel computations in SNNs suggests a focus on hardware and embedded systems (cs.ET) and emerging technologies (cs.EM). The paper also discusses the use of statistical models to improve the performance of the system, which falls under the category of applied statistics (cs.AR). Finally, the use of SNNs for image recognition suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
